fields.Title: PLAZA / TIRETRACKS VISCAL
fields.Description: You notice a set of a motor carriage tracks backing into the fence.

fields.Title: You: "This is where I started off with my..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is where I started off with my motor carriage.

fields.Title: You: "What happened next?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What happened next?

fields.Title: Authority: "The hole in this fence doesn't look..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The hole in this fence doesn't look *that* huge.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "...before heading south. Must have..."
fields.Dialogue Text: ...before heading south. Must have been in a hurry.

fields.Title: You: "Okay. What happened next?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Okay. What happened next?

fields.Title: You: ""This is where I started off with m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is where I started off with my motor carriage... before sinking it in the sea."

fields.Title: You: "I think I got it. [Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: I think I got it. [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: ""A car drove through the fence.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "A car drove through the fence."

fields.Title: You: ""This is the point of departure of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is the point of departure of the vehicle that crashed into the Samaran Butter sign."

fields.Title: You: "Why am I looking at this?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Why am I looking at this?

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "You could *follow* the tracks south..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You could *follow* the tracks south. There seems to be a canal there. See where they went. (If you find the time.)

fields.Title: Interfacing: "As a matter of fact, you don't even..."
fields.Dialogue Text: As a matter of fact, you don't even know why you stopped here. You would never drive recklessly like this. And you don't have a car.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The tyre tracks were left here by a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The tyre tracks were left here by an unknown event that took place some days ago. It's a message, written in the language of burnt rubber.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The driver proceeded to back out of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The driver proceeded to back out of the yard, barely stopping before hitting the adjacent building...

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Cop habit. You look at everything."
fields.Dialogue Text: Cop habit. You look at everything.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Hard to say. Your vision is blurred..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Hard to say. Your vision is blurred and you are having difficulty concentrating thanks to your relentless hangover.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Yes. And ended up half-sunken in th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes. And ended up half-sunken in the sea. You must have been drunk when you left off.

fields.Title: Authority: "He was exaggerating. People blame *..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He was exaggerating. People blame *cops* for everything that goes wrong in the world. This has nothing to do with you.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "No, these tracks are not interestin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, these tracks are not interesting at all. Let the street sweeper just sweep them away.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant follows the tracks w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant follows the tracks with his gaze. "That's plausible. A similar... reckless abandon seems to be in evidence."

fields.Title: You: "Damn bartender."
fields.Dialogue Text: Damn bartender.

fields.Title: You: "This is significant somehow."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is significant somehow.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Maybe. Probably."
fields.Dialogue Text: Maybe. Probably.

fields.Title: You: "Reconstruct the movement."
fields.Dialogue Text: Reconstruct the movement.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The tracks are as they have ever be..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The tracks are as they have ever been. A bit more worn, perhaps. Fortunately, the street sweeper still hasn't noticed their presence.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""You are correct. This is a rather..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You are correct. This is a rather motor carriage-friendly city."

fields.Title: You: "This is the point of departure of t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is the point of departure of the motor carriage that crashed into the Samaran Butter sign, right?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No wonder the cafeteria manager se..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No wonder the cafeteria manager seemed frustrated when he was giving us directions to the yard."

fields.Title: You: "Not now. [Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: Not now. [Leave.]

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "...and then accelerated straight in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: ...and then accelerated straight into the fence.
fields.Alternate1: ...and then accelerated straight into the fence. Left a hole *big enough for the Franconigerian cavalry,* according to the cafeteria manager.
fields.Alternate2: ...and then accelerated straight into the fence. Left a hole *big enough for the Franconigerian cavalry,* according to the cafeteria manager. (Why that pang of guilt again?)

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Somehow that makes you feel... scar..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Somehow that makes you feel... scared. You don't know why.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "You see a set of tyre tracks in the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You see a set of tyre tracks in the brown slush that covers the plaza mosaic.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Some of that rubber stuck to the ti..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Some of that rubber stuck to the tiles right in front of the Whirling-in-Rags. This is point A. The driver started there...

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "An ominous warning of bad things ah..."
fields.Dialogue Text: An ominous warning of bad things ahead.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Well," he gestures toward the gapi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well," he gestures toward the gaping hole in the fence, "you did provide us with a very convenient access point to the crime scene."

fields.Title: Logic: "This isn't case-related, you think."
fields.Dialogue Text: This isn't case-related, you think.

fields.Title: You: "What kind of vehicle drove through..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What kind of vehicle drove through here?

fields.Title: You: ""Is this connected to the case?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is this connected to the case?"

fields.Title: You: "The hole is not that impressive."
fields.Dialogue Text: The hole is not that impressive.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Why yes it is! Good connection."
fields.Dialogue Text: Why yes it is! Good connection.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yes, it is. Well," he gestures tow..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, it is. Well," he gestures toward the gaping hole in the fence, "you did provide us with a very convenient access point to the crime scene."

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Hard to say."
fields.Dialogue Text: Hard to say.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I'm not sure... there are plenty o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm not sure... there are plenty of traffic accidents waiting to happen in Martinaise. With the jam right here on the roundabout. I would keep them separate."
